3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with image processing techniques for thinning the Gauss image, which is a topic closely related to computer vision. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper deals with optimizing B-spline surfaces for paneling architectural surfaces, which is a topic closely related to computational engineering. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with enforcing rotational cylindrical, rotational conical and planar panels, which are topics closely related to control systems.
